{"serial": "09038", "department_serial": 3, "code": "GS3639", "class": "B", "name": {"en": "Immigration and Society: 1949", "ch": "移民與社會：一九四九專題"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Li, Kuang-Chun"], "ch": ["李廣均"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["5", "6"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "106"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "通識教育中心", "en": "General Education Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 12, "selected": 50, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "台灣是一個移民社會，不同時期的人口移動改變了台灣社會的歷史面貌與社會人口結構，也豐富了台灣的人文面貌。本課程的教學目標是從「移民與社會」的角度來介紹一九四九前後來台的「外省人」，提供修課學生具有知識基礎的觀點來認識這一波移民潮的特殊性與內在差異，講授主題包括代表性人物、歷史脈絡、人口與文化特徵、職業類型、居住空間、婚姻經驗、親屬與家庭網絡、經濟行為、階級組成、政治態度與行為、身份選擇、世代差異、眷村保存、移民理論等面向。", "en": "Taiwan is an immigrant society. The movement of people in different periods has changed the historical appearance and social demographic structure of Taiwan society and enriched the humanistic appearance of Taiwan. The purpose of this course is to introduce the “Mainlanders“ from the perspective of ““immigration and society““  to provide students a knowledge base to understand the particularity and their inner differences. Teaching topics include representative figures, historical eventst, soico-demoraphic and cultural characteristics, occupation type, living space, marriage experience, relatives and family networks, economic behavior, class composition, political attitudes and behavior, identity selection, generation gap, cultural preservation of chuan-tsun, immigration theory etc."}, "outline": {"ch": "“1.課程介紹\n2.代表性人物專題\n3.歷史脈絡、人口暨文化特徵\n4.婚姻、親屬暨家庭網絡\n5.職業類型與居住空間（一）\n6.職業類型與居住空間（一）\n7.影片欣賞：老莫的第二個春天/香蕉天堂\n8.經濟行為、階級組成\n9.政治態度與行為、身份選擇、世代差異\n10.考試\n11.影片欣賞：山有多高\n12.「眷村」保存的現況與挑戰（一）\n13.「眷村」保存的現況與挑戰（二）\n14.移民理論介紹與比較\n15.學期報告分享\n16.學期報告分享\n17.學期報告分享\n18.綜合討論“", "en": "1. Introduction to the course\n2. Representative characters\n3. Historical context, population and cultural characteristics\n4. marriage, family and family network\n5. Occupation type and living space (a)\n6. Occupation type and living space (a)\n7. Film appreciation: old Mo‘s second spring / banana paradise\n8. Economic behavior, class composition\n9. Political attitudes and behavior, identity selection, generation differences\n10. Exam\n11. Film appreciation: how high mountain?\n12. Status and Challenges for the Preservation of ““dependents““ (1)\n13. The status and challenges of the preservation of ““dependents““ (2)\n14. Introduction and comparison of immigration theory\n15. Semester report sharing\n16. term report sharing\n17. term report sharing\n18. Comprehensive discussion"}, "textbook": {"ch": "“指定教科書\n1.教師自編講義/LMS版\n2.無\n參考書目\nA/張茂桂編（2010）「國家與認同：一些外省人的觀點」。台北：群學出版社。\nB/李廣均編（2010）「離與苦：戰爭的延續」。台北：群學出版社。\nC/張翰璧編（2011）「扶桑花與家園想像」。台北：群學出版社。\nD/李廣均（2011）““第五章：外省人““ 收錄於蕭新煌編「臺灣全志．卷三住民志．族群篇」，頁367-430，2011年11月。南投：國史館臺灣文獻館。\nE/李廣均（2015）＜台灣「眷村」的歷史形成與社會差異：列管眷村與自力眷村的比較＞《台灣社會學刊》57：129-172\nF/李廣均（2017）＜文化、歷史與多元：關於國軍眷村保存的一些觀察與思考＞《文化資產保存學刊》39：89-101。“", "en": "self-edited handouts\noptional references\nA / Zhang Maogui (2010) ““State and identity: some view of foreigners.““ Taipei: group publishing press.\nB / Li Guangjun (2010) ““from the bitter: the continuation of the war.““ Taipei: group publishing press.\nC / Zhang Hanbi (2011) ““Hibiscus and home imagination““. Taipei: group publishing press.\nD / Li Guangjun (2011) ““Chapter 5: Foreigners““ are included in Xiao Xinhuang, ““Taiwan.““ Three volumes of the people of the people. ““Articles 367 - 430, November 2011. Nantou: National Museum of Taiwan Museum of literature.\nE / Li Guangjun (2015) ““The Formation and Social Differences of Taiwan‘s““ Village ““: A Comparative Study of the Departments and Self-reliance Departments> Taiwan Journal of Social Sciences 57: 129-172\nF / Li Guangjun (2017)"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%",